<TITLE> MPO salaries to be adjusted to new pay scale </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  Teachers and employees of educational institutions enlisted under the government's monthly pay order (MPO) programme will get pay hikes in line with the new national pay scale. The education ministry on Sunday issued a circular giving retrospective effect to the new pay scale from July 1 last year, said ministry spokesperson Subodh Chandra Dhali. The government implemented the Seventh National Pay Scale from July 1 last year initially keeping teachers and employees of MPO educational institutions out of its purview, as it was thinking of formulating a separate pay scale for them. The circular said, with the new implementation, monthly salary of MPO teachers or employees, who receive 100 percent of the basic salary from the government and other benefits from the institution's own funds, would increase by no less than Tk 2,000. It also said dearness allowance that the teachers and employees are now receiving, in lieu of pay rise, would go from the day of implementation of the new pay scale, with adjustments. b
